+{"id":"frankenpandas-sjeh1","title":"fd90.169: README df.column(name)? wrong — column returns Option","description":"fd90.74-168 README audit. Line 1528 in Selection and Indexing shows:

  let col = df.column("price")?;             // Single column as &Column

But crates/fp-frame/src/lib.rs:16242 declares:
  pub fn column(&self, name: &str) -> Option<&Column>

The question-mark operator on Option only works in functions that return Option (or another Try-impl). In a typical Result-returning function, applying it to an Option hits:
  error[E0277]: the question-mark operator can only be used on Option in a function that returns Option
  the trait FromResidual is not implemented for Result

A user copy-pasting hits a confusing compile error. Fix: use .expect() to surface the missing-column case explicitly so the example compiles in any context. Pure README change.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T16:42:44.357485650Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T16:44:27.876068245Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T16:44:27.872704831Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
